# copy paste scenarios

install gvim to enable '+'-register in vim
or compile a vim version that supports registers


scenarios
---------
copy from / paste into


from/into	vim	cli	gui
vim		1	2	3
command line	4	5	6
gui application	7	8	9


1 vim - vim
-----------

1 manual selection
2 whole line
3 v-block

vim registers can have names a-z

		1	2	3
select		v  	V	c-v	(v-block)
copy 		y	yy	"ay	('a' register)
cut		d	dd	"ad	
paste		p	p	"ap


3 vim - gui
-----------

		1	2	3
select		v	V	c-v		
copy 			"+y		('+' register)
cut			"+d
paste			c-v	


7 gui - vim
-----------

		1	2	3
select	
copy		c-c
cut		c-x
paste		"+p	c-a-v

